                                        <comments>
                            <comment id="97065" author="deki" created="Wed, 8 Jan 2014 01:04:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Should be done for the next version. It&apos;s confusing to have xml errors after upgrading to Spring 4 and no information in the documentation what happened to idref/ local.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="97390" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Thu, 16 Jan 2014 02:10:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In fact, &apos;idref&apos; is still available and checked against actually registered bean names at runtime. We&apos;re turning it into a RuntimeBeanNameReference in Spring&apos;s model, whereas a standard &apos;ref&apos; gets turned into a RuntimeBeanReference.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As for the &apos;local&apos; attribute, I&apos;ve added the following note to the ref docs:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The `local` attribute on the `ref` element is no longer supported in the 4.0 beans xsd since it does not provide value over a regular `bean` reference anymore. Simply change your existing `ref local` references to `ref bean` when upgrading to the 4.0 schema.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
